<subSubSection id="C36E64D8D4389A3D42BCFA4AFBF952CD" box="[201,1088,1416,1440]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCB3753D4389A3D42BCFA4AFBF952CD" blockId="14.[151,1436,510,1440]" box="[201,1088,1416,1440]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B900EB41D4389A3D42BCFA4AFEE952CD" bold="true" box="[201,336,1416,1440]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin name for the peacock.
